CONFIDENTIAL SETTLEMENT AGREEMENT AND RELEASE

This Confidential Settlement Agreement and Release ("Agreement") is entered into on February 12, 2025, between NIMMO & ASSOCIATES FERTILITY CLINIC, P.C., a Massachusetts professional corporation ("Clinic"), and JENNIFER and MICHAEL RICHARDS, individually ("Claimants").

RECITALS

WHEREAS, Claimants have asserted claims against Clinic arising from fertility treatment provided to Jennifer Richards during 2023-2024;

WHEREAS, Clinic denies all liability and wrongdoing but desires to resolve the dispute to avoid the costs and uncertainties of litigation;

WHEREAS, the parties wish to compromise and settle their disputes upon the terms set forth herein;

NOW, THEREFORE, in consideration of the mutual covenants contained herein, the parties agree as follows:

1. SETTLEMENT PAYMENT

1.1 Payment Amount. Clinic shall pay to Claimants the total sum of Four Hundred Fifty Thousand Dollars ($450,000) (the "Settlement Amount").

1.2 Payment Terms. The Settlement Amount shall be paid as follows:
(a) $200,000 within 30 days of execution of this Agreement
(b) $125,000 within 90 days of execution
(c) $125,000 within 180 days of execution

1.3 Payment Method. All payments shall be made by certified check payable to "Jennifer and Michael Richards" and delivered to their counsel.

2. RELEASE OF CLAIMS

2.1 General Release. In consideration of the Settlement Amount, Claimants hereby release and forever discharge Clinic, its officers, directors, employees, agents, insurers, and affiliates from any and all claims, demands, causes of action, damages, costs, expenses, and liabilities of any kind arising from or related to the fertility treatment provided to Jennifer Richards.

2.2 Scope of Release. The release includes, but is not limited to, claims for:
(a) Medical malpractice and negligence
(b) Lack of informed consent
(c) Emotional distress and pain and suffering
(d) Loss of consortium
(e) Medical expenses and lost wages
(f) Future medical costs and treatment

2.3 Unknown Claims. This release extends to claims that are presently unknown or unsuspected, and Claimants expressly waive any rights under applicable law regarding unknown claims.

3. CONFIDENTIALITY

3.1 Non-Disclosure. The parties agree that the terms of this Agreement, the Settlement Amount, and all negotiations leading to this Agreement shall remain strictly confidential.

3.2 Permitted Disclosures. The confidentiality provisions shall not prevent disclosure:
(a) To immediate family members who agree to maintain confidentiality
(b) To financial advisors and tax preparers for legitimate purposes
(c) As required by law or court order
(d) To insurance carriers for coverage purposes

3.3 Non-Disparagement. Claimants agree not to make any public statements that disparage or negatively reflect upon Clinic, its staff, or its medical care.

4. MEDICAL RECORDS

4.1 Return of Records. Claimants shall return all medical records and copies obtained during the course of treatment or litigation within 30 days.

4.2 Destruction of Copies. All electronic and physical copies of medical records in possession of Claimants or their representatives shall be destroyed.

5. NO ADMISSION OF LIABILITY

This Agreement does not constitute an admission of liability, wrongdoing, or fault by any party. Clinic specifically denies any liability for the claims asserted.

6. COOPERATION

6.1 Regulatory Proceedings. If any regulatory body investigates the treatment provided to Jennifer Richards, Claimants agree to cooperate fully and provide truthful information.

6.2 Future Medical Care. Nothing in this Agreement prevents Claimants from seeking future medical care from other providers for fertility-related issues.

7. LEGAL REPRESENTATION

Each party acknowledges that they have been represented by competent legal counsel in negotiating this Agreement and have been advised of their legal rights.

8. ENTIRE AGREEMENT

This Agreement constitutes the entire agreement between the parties and supersedes all prior negotiations, representations, or agreements relating to the subject matter hereof.

9. GOVERNING LAW

This Agreement shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of the Commonwealth of Massachusetts.

10. ENFORCEABILITY

If any provision of this Agreement is deemed unenforceable, the remaining provisions shall remain in full force and effect.

11. BINDING EFFECT

This Agreement shall be binding upon the parties and their heirs, successors, and assigns.

12. COUNTERPART EXECUTION

This Agreement may be executed in counterparts, each of which shall be deemed an original and all of which together shall constitute one agreement.

IN WITNESS WHEREOF, the parties have executed this Agreement on the date first written above.

